data.title: Cheryl Fernandez-Versini and Jean-Bernard finalise divorce
data.meta_description: The Girls Aloud star said her second husband's unreasonable behaviour - during a marriage of 19 months - led her to lose weight.
data.text:
Cheryl Fernandez-Versini's divorce from French restaurateur Jean-Bernard Versini has been finalised.

The former X Factor judge and Girls Aloud singer had complained of her 35-year-old husband's unreasonable behaviour, saying it had caused her "stress and weight loss", court papers showed.

The pair, who were together for 19 months, were granted a decree nisi in a London hearing that lasted 14 seconds. Neither attended.

It is Fernandez-Versini's second divorce.

The 33-year-old had previously been married to footballer Ashley Cole for four years before their divorce in 2010.

Four years later she married Jean-Bernard in a secret beach wedding, but by the following year they had split.

Fernandez-Versini has been in a relationship with One Direction star Liam Payne since last December.
